     <h1>Economics &amp; Business</h1> 
     <h3><img src="images/D1X_9102_000.jpg" alt="Economics and Business Department" width="505" height="458" align="middle"></h3> 
     <h3><em> Clockwise from top: Edd Noell, John Tynan, Coby Harmon, Jim Morouse, Paul Morgan, Heather Rupp, Rick Ifland, David Olson, Ramon Gupta, Enrico Manlapig. </em></h3> 
     <h3>&nbsp;</h3> 
     <p>Students majoring in Economics and Business at Westmont find a highly collaborative, friendly environment that provides a healthy blend of quantitative analysis and theory with practical application in the marketplace.&nbsp; Active engagement both inside and outside the classroom, with interested and attentive professors, is the norm.&nbsp; Students are gaining the information and expertise that make them better contributors and communicators – information and expertise that prepare them for fascinating and gratifying careers.</p> 
     <p><strong></strong><strong>Career Choices</strong></p> 
     <p>Our graduates have distinguished themselves as leaders across a wide range of industries throughout the world, from Fortune 500 companies to Silicon Valley start-ups in the fields of accounting, finance, marketing, social entrepreneurship, business development, management, and law, to name just a few. For some information on the work of some of our alumni, please see <a href="alumni-careers.html">these profiles</a>.</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;<u></u>Rick Ifland  Department Chairman </p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <p style="text-align:center;"><em><br> </em></p> 
